text: Dipsas pakaraima is an arboreal snake of the family Dipsadidae. It has been placed in the Dipsas temporalis group. It is native to medium and higher elevations in west-central Guyana. It has been collected in Kaieteur National Park and Mount Ayanganna. Its food probably consists of snails and slugs. ==References== pakaraima Category:Snakes of South America Category:Reptiles described in 2004 Category:Reptiles of Guyana Category:Endemic fauna of Guyana
